        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued March 30 at 3:04PM CDT until March 30 at 3:15PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles west of
Louisville, or 11 miles northwest of Flora, moving northeast at 60
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Emergency management.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Wakefield, Wendelin, Bible Grove, Flora Municipal Airport, Sailor
Springs, Flora, Louisville, Ingraham, Iola, Clay City, Hord, and
Xenia.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for south central
and southeastern Illinois.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
